1
00:01:31,200 --> 00:01:34,918
=Vanished Name=

2
00:01:35,000 --> 00:01:37,835
=Episode 20=
(The Trap)

3
00:01:38,994 --> 00:01:39,494
Right.

4
00:01:40,474 --> 00:01:41,713
Why don't we call Xiaoming?

5
00:01:42,353 --> 00:01:44,353
He Yuqiong gave me her number,
but I never called.

6
00:01:44,674 --> 00:01:46,713
(Ren Xiaoming)
Since you're here, let's surprise her.

7
00:01:51,153 --> 00:01:51,674
Forget it.

8
00:01:52,834 --> 00:01:54,153
I don't want her to know

9
00:01:54,674 --> 00:01:55,513
that I'm in La City

10
00:01:56,634 --> 00:01:57,674
and come to find me.

11
00:01:59,274 --> 00:01:59,774
Okay.

12
00:02:00,394 --> 00:02:00,894
Oh, right.

13
00:02:02,593 --> 00:02:04,674
Could you enter her phone number?

14
00:02:05,313 --> 00:02:06,153
I'd like to save it.

15
00:02:15,858 --> 00:02:19,445
(Ren Xiaoming, saving)

16
00:02:23,313 --> 00:02:24,153
I know.

17
00:02:24,713 --> 00:02:25,674
You don't contact us,

18
00:02:26,674 --> 00:02:27,873
so we don't worry.

19
00:02:29,354 --> 00:02:30,994
Call for help if your heart acts up.

20
00:02:31,313 --> 00:02:32,713
Don't tough it out alone.

21
00:02:35,794 --> 00:02:38,753
I'm just fine. Don't worry about me.

22
00:02:44,234 --> 00:02:45,234
Well, that's it.

23
00:02:45,554 --> 00:02:47,153
I-I'm leaving.

24
00:02:47,633 --> 00:02:49,313
Don't stay out here. It's windy.

25
00:02:57,913 --> 00:02:59,994
(Xiaoming, how's everything going?)

26
00:03:01,313 --> 00:03:02,680
(Is Qingzhou University pretty?)

27
00:03:03,674 --> 00:03:04,954
(What are your roommates like?)

28
00:03:13,153 --> 00:03:14,153
(I won't go to Qingzhou.)

29
00:03:14,954 --> 00:03:16,033
(Studying here)

30
00:03:16,633 --> 00:03:17,394
(is just fine.)

31
00:03:24,873 --> 00:03:25,713
Listen to me.

32
00:03:26,234 --> 00:03:28,913
Stop flaunting your wealth
in front of Xiaoming.

33
00:03:29,593 --> 00:03:31,753
It's so awkward
to pay for her stuff at the mall.

34
00:03:32,313 --> 00:03:34,274
She only has 600 yuan a month.

35
00:03:34,274 --> 00:03:35,834
How could I let her spend money?

36
00:03:35,834 --> 00:03:36,873
I meant well.

37
00:03:37,554 --> 00:03:39,554
Honestly, I also feel awkward,

38
00:03:39,873 --> 00:03:41,153
scared of misspeaking.

39
00:03:41,394 --> 00:03:42,354
What should we do?

40
00:03:42,794 --> 00:03:44,954
Maybe we don't invite her next time?

41
00:03:45,593 --> 00:03:48,514
Or maybe we can come up
with a code word or something.

42
00:03:49,153 --> 00:03:49,994
Like what?

43
00:03:52,193 --> 00:03:53,834
(I know they mean well.)

44
00:03:54,433 --> 00:03:55,753
(But it still hurts.)

45
00:03:57,193 --> 00:04:00,114
(It won't do.
I must have more jobs to make money.)

46
00:04:01,593 --> 00:04:03,354
Life's got no answer? Grab a beer.

47
00:04:03,593 --> 00:04:05,074
We're running a promotion.

48
00:04:05,074 --> 00:04:06,473
Would you like to learn about it?

49
00:04:06,753 --> 00:04:08,954
We have discounts. Want to take a look?

50
00:04:08,954 --> 00:04:09,394
No need.

51
00:04:09,394 --> 00:04:11,234
Take a sip of our brew.
Forget your worries.

52
00:04:11,994 --> 00:04:13,633
(Someone came to steal my business.)

53
00:04:15,433 --> 00:04:16,714
(And she took my spot.)

54
00:04:18,633 --> 00:04:20,513
You think I took your spot, don't you?

55
00:04:20,994 --> 00:04:25,193
- Can you read minds?
- You're also from Qingzhou University?

56
00:04:26,594 --> 00:04:29,073
I'm Liang Yi, from Law Faculty,
admitted in 2007. And you?

57
00:04:30,674 --> 00:04:32,154
Ren Xiaoming, from EM Faculty,
admitted in 2007.

58
00:04:32,154 --> 00:04:33,753
Now we know each other.

59
00:04:34,513 --> 00:04:35,354
Still so many?

60
00:04:35,354 --> 00:04:37,313
You won't finish it until midnight.

61
00:04:37,513 --> 00:04:38,474
Let me help you.

62
00:04:38,714 --> 00:04:40,674
Finish early and we can grab a drink.

63
00:04:41,154 --> 00:04:42,953
Don't miss out if you're passing by.

64
00:04:43,393 --> 00:04:45,354
Last day of the promotion.
Buy one and get one free.

65
00:04:45,354 --> 00:04:47,193
Don't miss out if you're passing by.

66
00:04:47,234 --> 00:04:48,953
Life's got no answer? Grab a beer.

67
00:04:49,193 --> 00:04:51,034
Take a sip of our brew.
Forget your worries.

68
00:04:53,833 --> 00:04:54,513
(Xiaoming.)

69
00:04:55,273 --> 00:04:57,554
(What do you do
when you're not in class?)

70
00:04:58,273 --> 00:05:00,073
(Have you seen
royal gardens in Qingzhou?)

71
00:05:01,234 --> 00:05:02,554
(Have you made new friends?)

72
00:05:15,714 --> 00:05:17,753
What's wrong with Xiaoming today?

73
00:05:17,953 --> 00:05:19,674
She's usually on time.

74
00:05:27,994 --> 00:05:28,994
Xiaoming, over here.

75
00:05:29,513 --> 00:05:30,633
Why are you there?

76
00:05:30,633 --> 00:05:31,614
Come over here.

77
00:05:32,073 --> 00:05:32,573
Over there.

78
00:05:39,994 --> 00:05:40,794
Hurry up.

79
00:05:40,953 --> 00:05:42,193
Why are you hiding here?

80
00:05:42,554 --> 00:05:43,994
Why are you so late?

81
00:05:44,154 --> 00:05:46,073
I've been looking for you.

82
00:05:46,154 --> 00:05:48,433
It looked like an egg,
so I didn't dare come in.

83
00:05:49,873 --> 00:05:50,994
Sorry, I'm late.

84
00:05:51,594 --> 00:05:53,273
No worries. We just got here, too.

85
00:05:54,594 --> 00:05:55,736
Let me introduce you.

86
00:05:56,054 --> 00:05:58,114
This is Ren Xiaoming from your faculty.

87
00:05:58,753 --> 00:06:00,154
You're from our EM faculty?

88
00:06:00,513 --> 00:06:01,193
Hello, Senior.

89
00:06:02,114 --> 00:06:02,614
Hello.

90
00:06:03,594 --> 00:06:06,513
He's not a senior. He's
Professor Zhuang's Teaching Assistant.

91
00:06:07,674 --> 00:06:08,273
I'll call him

92
00:06:08,474 --> 00:06:09,073
Mr. Liu?

93
00:06:09,633 --> 00:06:10,424
Hello, Mr. Liu.

94
00:06:10,753 --> 00:06:11,474
That's too formal.

95
00:06:12,273 --> 00:06:13,354
I haven't taught you.

96
00:06:13,674 --> 00:06:15,914
Just call me Xiaoran. Be casual.

97
00:06:17,893 --> 00:06:18,393
Alright.

98
00:06:18,393 --> 00:06:19,393
Sit down.

99
00:06:19,393 --> 00:06:20,753
Look at you, all nervous.

100
00:06:21,273 --> 00:06:22,073
How silly.

101
00:06:23,953 --> 00:06:24,873
It's only natural.

102
00:06:25,474 --> 00:06:26,633
Everyone gets nervous here.

103
00:06:27,393 --> 00:06:28,034
Me too.

104
00:06:29,034 --> 00:06:29,994
I was just strolling,

105
00:06:30,114 --> 00:06:31,994
circling this place around and around.

106
00:06:32,154 --> 00:06:33,914
It's like tracing a strand of DNA.

107
00:06:34,234 --> 00:06:35,433
Then suddenly, I saw this.

108
00:06:36,674 --> 00:06:39,234
"What is this? It's an egg?

109
00:06:39,633 --> 00:06:40,952
What does it mean?

110
00:06:41,583 --> 00:06:44,833
Are we going to be cornered
or trapped in our own web?"

111
00:06:47,633 --> 00:06:48,354
Just kidding.

112
00:06:50,034 --> 00:06:50,554
Oh, right.

113
00:06:51,193 --> 00:06:53,714
Xiaoran, you were talking
about Borges earlier. Go on.

114
00:06:57,154 --> 00:07:00,234
Not everyone's interested
in hearing about Borges.

115
00:07:00,554 --> 00:07:02,594
Xiaoming, are you interested in Borges?

116
00:07:03,154 --> 00:07:03,674
I'm all ears.

117
00:07:04,034 --> 00:07:04,633
Really?

118
00:07:05,594 --> 00:07:08,193
Then perhaps you also wish to be

119
00:07:08,513 --> 00:07:11,273
a nightingale with a dreamlike maze.

120
00:07:13,362 --> 00:07:15,073
(Qingzhou, 2023)

121
00:07:15,073 --> 00:07:17,034
Mr. Liu, what are you...

122
00:07:18,433 --> 00:07:20,433
- I'm here to see her, Ms. Liang.
- She's busy.

123
00:07:20,433 --> 00:07:20,994
Relax.

124
00:07:20,994 --> 00:07:21,753
It'll be fast.

125
00:07:21,753 --> 00:07:22,914
I'll let her know.

126
00:07:22,914 --> 00:07:24,393
No need. Just one minute.

127
00:07:24,833 --> 00:07:25,554
Ms. Liang.

128
00:07:26,833 --> 00:07:27,633
Excuse us.

129
00:07:28,393 --> 00:07:29,234
Keep the door open.

130
00:07:29,554 --> 00:07:30,873
I am Ren Xiaoming's lawyer.

131
00:07:31,193 --> 00:07:33,234
We can't meet privately
before the divorce hearing.

132
00:07:33,513 --> 00:07:34,073
Tan Xin.

133
00:07:34,433 --> 00:07:34,933
Ms. Liang.

134
00:07:35,914 --> 00:07:37,873
Record everything Mr. Liu and I discuss.

135
00:07:42,753 --> 00:07:45,234
We go way back. Is this necessary?

136
00:07:46,073 --> 00:07:47,114
We're not that close.

137
00:07:48,193 --> 00:07:49,154
We're both adults.

138
00:07:49,273 --> 00:07:50,753
So respect the rules, okay?

139
00:07:54,474 --> 00:07:55,313
I came here

140
00:07:56,393 --> 00:07:57,873
just to advise you

141
00:07:58,433 --> 00:07:59,753
not to pursue this lawsuit.

142
00:08:00,594 --> 00:08:01,994
Because you can't win.

143
00:08:03,594 --> 00:08:05,240
You're talking to the wrong person.

144
00:08:05,594 --> 00:08:06,914
The divorce is up to your wife.

145
00:08:06,953 --> 00:08:08,753
Whether I take the case is up to me.

146
00:08:09,433 --> 00:08:11,714
Ms. Liang,
I know you're a capable lawyer.

147
00:08:11,953 --> 00:08:13,393
But let me ask you something.

148
00:08:13,914 --> 00:08:16,433
If the plaintiff is at fault
for having an affair,

149
00:08:16,433 --> 00:08:18,554
who do you think the law protects?

150
00:08:19,234 --> 00:08:20,594
If you dare smear her name,

151
00:08:20,674 --> 00:08:22,073
I'll sue you into the ground.

152
00:08:22,594 --> 00:08:23,753
Don't rush to say that.

153
00:08:26,273 --> 00:08:27,114
Look at this first.

154
00:08:32,273 --> 00:08:33,954
(Transfer)
During the marriage,

155
00:08:34,273 --> 00:08:36,793
she made irregular transfers
to a specific male.

156
00:08:37,074 --> 00:08:38,234
Over the years,

157
00:08:38,434 --> 00:08:41,994
the cumulative amount
reached six figures.

158
00:08:42,994 --> 00:08:44,873
What would you call that?

159
00:08:46,633 --> 00:08:47,553
Please leave.

160
00:08:49,074 --> 00:08:50,793
Be more polite.

161
00:08:51,114 --> 00:08:52,074
We're on camera.

162
00:08:53,153 --> 00:08:55,074
I hate to air
my dirty laundry in public.

163
00:08:55,354 --> 00:08:56,913
I came here today

164
00:08:57,114 --> 00:08:59,153
just to tell you

165
00:08:59,793 --> 00:09:01,314
that I don't want Ren Xiaoming

166
00:09:01,633 --> 00:09:04,954
to end up destroying herself.

167
00:09:06,074 --> 00:09:08,954
Ms. Liang, she is my wife.

168
00:09:09,153 --> 00:09:12,114
As an old classmate,
please don't make things worse.

169
00:09:13,553 --> 00:09:15,913
I will verify what you've said
with my client.

170
00:09:15,954 --> 00:09:18,994
But please don't interfere with my work
before the hearing.

171
00:09:19,994 --> 00:09:20,513
Fine.

172
00:09:21,194 --> 00:09:23,753
If you insist on this lawsuit,
I'll see it through.

173
00:09:24,114 --> 00:09:25,273
Don't say I didn't warn you.

174
00:09:25,474 --> 00:09:28,314
You're the one
who's going to end up humiliated.

175
00:09:29,834 --> 00:09:30,840
Are you threatening me?

176
00:09:33,434 --> 00:09:34,673
How could I dare?

177
00:09:35,913 --> 00:09:36,513
Good luck.

178
00:09:38,273 --> 00:09:38,834
Bye.

179
00:09:46,114 --> 00:09:46,968
Give me your phone.

180
00:09:51,074 --> 00:09:51,994
Over the years,

181
00:09:52,194 --> 00:09:54,393
the cumulative amount
reached six figures.

182
00:09:54,793 --> 00:09:56,114
What would you call that?

183
00:10:00,393 --> 00:10:01,273
No cloud save, huh?

184
00:10:01,393 --> 00:10:01,913
No.

185
00:10:02,194 --> 00:10:03,214
Okay, thanks.

186
00:10:09,834 --> 00:10:10,954
Six figures.

187
00:10:12,834 --> 00:10:14,354
(Way to go, Ren Xiaoming.)

188
00:10:15,194 --> 00:10:17,434
(You hid such important information
from me.)

189
00:10:36,033 --> 00:10:37,474
Did you date someone in college?

190
00:10:38,074 --> 00:10:38,753
What's wrong?

191
00:10:39,673 --> 00:10:40,753
Nothing, just chatting.

192
00:10:42,673 --> 00:10:43,673
Yeah, I did.

193
00:10:44,434 --> 00:10:45,393
When?

194
00:10:45,793 --> 00:10:47,553
How could I remember? It was ages ago.

195
00:10:48,114 --> 00:10:49,714
We have met since the freshman year.

196
00:10:49,714 --> 00:10:50,594
Why haven't I heard?

197
00:10:52,753 --> 00:10:55,234
What's with you today?
Why keep harping on this?

198
00:10:56,194 --> 00:10:57,194
I'm just curious.

199
00:10:57,753 --> 00:11:00,594
On a personal level, I'm a close friend
you can confide in.

200
00:11:01,513 --> 00:11:02,234
Professionally,

201
00:11:03,393 --> 00:11:04,834
I'm your divorce lawyer.

202
00:11:05,153 --> 00:11:08,513
I need you to be honest with me.

203
00:11:12,673 --> 00:11:13,994
What do you want to know?

204
00:11:16,033 --> 00:11:17,033
Is there a third party?

205
00:11:18,393 --> 00:11:19,834
How do you define "third party"?

206
00:11:20,194 --> 00:11:23,194
Interfering in a marriage
makes you a third party.

207
00:11:25,434 --> 00:11:26,553
That counts?

208
00:11:29,273 --> 00:11:30,714
Then every marriage has one.

209
00:11:33,633 --> 00:11:34,714
The phone.

210
00:11:36,194 --> 00:11:38,673
You spend more time
looking at your phone, don't you?

211
00:11:38,913 --> 00:11:40,994
You know I'm talking about a person.

212
00:11:41,553 --> 00:11:43,753
The one you keep thinking about.

213
00:11:45,033 --> 00:11:47,234
Is there such a person?

214
00:11:59,234 --> 00:11:59,793
You're back.

215
00:12:00,954 --> 00:12:01,513
Let's eat.

216
00:12:02,753 --> 00:12:04,434
Another cooking livestream task today?

217
00:12:05,474 --> 00:12:06,834
If we really get divorced,

218
00:12:08,194 --> 00:12:11,074
it wouldn't be appropriate for me
to come and cook for you.

219
00:12:12,273 --> 00:12:14,273
Don't you like the food I make?

220
00:12:14,513 --> 00:12:15,013
Come on.

221
00:12:15,994 --> 00:12:16,714
Let's eat.

222
00:12:16,994 --> 00:12:18,354
We should enjoy each meal

223
00:12:18,834 --> 00:12:20,153
while we can.

224
00:12:20,994 --> 00:12:22,194
Playing the emotional card?

225
00:12:22,633 --> 00:12:23,273
Not at all.

226
00:12:23,793 --> 00:12:25,954
You're holding all the aces now.

227
00:12:26,594 --> 00:12:27,954
How can I possibly win?

228
00:12:30,474 --> 00:12:31,474
It's not that simple.

229
00:12:32,474 --> 00:12:34,434
You don't just have the aces.

230
00:12:34,434 --> 00:12:35,594
You've got four deuces too.

231
00:12:36,714 --> 00:12:39,074
You've got a great hand.
What can possibly scare you?

232
00:12:39,553 --> 00:12:41,594
Didn't you show Liang Yi
your cards today?

233
00:12:42,474 --> 00:12:44,913
I did that for your own good.

234
00:12:46,673 --> 00:12:48,114
You know about my "lover"

235
00:12:48,753 --> 00:12:51,033
and that I've been sending him money.

236
00:12:52,194 --> 00:12:53,834
You really don't mind it?

237
00:12:56,393 --> 00:12:57,194
No, I don't.

238
00:12:59,553 --> 00:13:01,793
Then I'll bring him to see you.

239
00:13:02,513 --> 00:13:04,873
- Would you cook for us?
- Sure.

240
00:13:05,553 --> 00:13:08,074
I'll cook for him
as long as we're still together.

241
00:13:10,314 --> 00:13:11,393
Find someone, too.

242
00:13:11,913 --> 00:13:12,633
Why should I?

243
00:13:12,793 --> 00:13:13,434
To be four.

244
00:13:13,714 --> 00:13:14,273
What for?

245
00:13:14,474 --> 00:13:15,314
To play mahjong.

246
00:13:15,314 --> 00:13:15,834
Of course.

247
00:13:17,753 --> 00:13:18,753
You're going too far.

248
00:13:21,273 --> 00:13:22,114
I find you

249
00:13:22,834 --> 00:13:23,594
quite interesting.

250
00:13:24,393 --> 00:13:25,513
You're having an affair.

251
00:13:25,714 --> 00:13:28,594
What right do you have
to ask me if I mind it?

252
00:13:29,033 --> 00:13:31,434
Would you be
having an affair if you cared?

253
00:13:35,273 --> 00:13:36,234
You still don't know

254
00:13:36,234 --> 00:13:37,434
what I care about most, huh?

255
00:13:38,553 --> 00:13:39,474
My image is ruined.

256
00:13:40,194 --> 00:13:41,913
My career is doomed, and I'm broke.

257
00:13:43,273 --> 00:13:44,033
What's left for me?

258
00:13:44,513 --> 00:13:45,033
Right?

259
00:13:47,673 --> 00:13:49,354
I have to settle for something.

260
00:13:50,354 --> 00:13:51,994
I have to hold onto things

261
00:13:51,994 --> 00:13:53,273
that can still be mine.

262
00:13:55,033 --> 00:13:57,114
So you think that in marriage,

263
00:13:57,594 --> 00:14:00,153
pride, status, property, and image

264
00:14:00,434 --> 00:14:01,753
are more important than love?

265
00:14:02,354 --> 00:14:03,594
Love doesn't matter.

266
00:14:03,793 --> 00:14:05,814
Having those things is enough, right?

267
00:14:06,234 --> 00:14:07,074
You're accusing me?

268
00:14:07,913 --> 00:14:08,913
Are you the type

269
00:14:09,114 --> 00:14:10,753
who wants love but not bread?

270
00:14:11,994 --> 00:14:14,474
You wanted money when you were young.

271
00:14:14,673 --> 00:14:16,793
Now you think you're financially free,

272
00:14:16,913 --> 00:14:18,074
and you want love instead?

273
00:14:21,114 --> 00:14:22,153
Ms. Ren.

274
00:14:23,673 --> 00:14:24,633
You know what they say.

275
00:14:27,673 --> 00:14:28,834
Life isn't easy.

276
00:14:28,913 --> 00:14:30,913
Someone is bearing the hardship for you.

277
00:14:31,474 --> 00:14:33,114
I'm the one bearing the hardship.

278
00:14:33,633 --> 00:14:34,553
I spent

279
00:14:34,633 --> 00:14:37,594
